records.addlTxt: Competency hearing on November 11, 2022 at 11:00 am.

9:02 AM Attorney Mark Emil Kershek in court for Jessica A Lopez. District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Abigail Kincheloe.  Defendant Jessica A Lopez not in court. 

Defense does not know where the Defendant is today, but believes there was confusion re: the 10/04/2022 hearing that was already set as a competency hearing. Defense requests to leave case on as set for 10/04/2022 for the competency hearing. Defense is unsure what the Defendant's treatment status is. 

State does not object to leaving 10/04/2022 hearing on. 
Defense will advise competency hearing will be needed. 
State advises that Dr. has not yet been subpoenaed. 

Court will issue, but stay a capias to 10/04/2022 hearing. 

Defendant appears at 9:06 am. Court passes case for Atty Kershek to speak to the Defendant. 

Case-recalled at 9:18 am. The Defendant appears. Court quashes capias. 

Defense advises that the Defendant has been in treatment with DHS, and is not contesting competency at this time. Defense requests to leave 10/04/2022 hearing on. 
Court requests that Defense be in contact with the State re: status of competency hearing. 
10/04/2022 hearing left on as set.

CONDITION ADDED ON 08/19/2022:
Defendant to go to DHHS for evaluation for Mental Health and Medication. 

Defendant to have no contact with victim A listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key.  Defendant is not to share, reproduce or distribute any personal and/or identifying information about the crime victim(s), except to their attorney.   Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.

Defendant Jessica A Lopez in court.  Attorney Mark Emil Kershek in court for Jessica A Lopez.  Attorney Melissa Zilavy in court for State of Wisconsin. Victim rights have been complied with by the Waukesha County District Attorneys Office. 

Both counsel discuss possible outcomes of case. 

Case moves to dismiss 22CM496 without prejudice, and requests that the Defendant have bond conditions modified on 22CM497 to include that she go to DHHS for evaluation for Mental Health and Medication. 

Defense agrees. 

Court conducts colloquy with Defendant re: competency. 

Based on Defendant's responses, the Court will withhold a competency finding today, set a status hearing and set a competency hearing. 

Court will dismiss 22CM496 without prejudice, and will modify the bond on 22CM497 include DHHS for evaluation for Mental Health and Medication. Defendant to be released forthwith.
